-- Yen Gains Versus Euro, Dollar as Asian Stocks Decline for a Second Day
-- B y   C a n d i c e   Z a c h a r i a h s
-- 2012-02-28T01:02:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-28/yen-gains-versus-euro-dollar-as-asian-stocks-decline-for-a-second-day.html
The yen advanced versus the euro and
dollar as Asian stocks slid for a second day, boosting demand
for the Japanese currency as a haven.  The yen gained 0.3 percent to 107.63 per euro as of 9:59
a.m. in  Tokyo  and rose 0.4 percent to 80.32 against the
greenback. The MSCI Asia Pacific Index of shares dropped 0.3
percent, after declining 0.5 percent yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candice Zachariahs in Sydney at 
